    "is_free": false,
    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You live inside a mechanical ladybird called a Clomper, which you can control by making pipes to power machines with steam. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2349380/extras/59855e22d4783448bcafbdf82ab73dd7.poster.avif?t=1759006490\" width=616 height=184 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2349380/extras/59855e22d4783448bcafbdf82ab73dd7.webm?t=1759006490\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2349380/extras/59855e22d4783448bcafbdf82ab73dd7.mp4?t=1759006490\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The outside world is a hellscape, which you explore from inside the Clomper. Leaving would kill you instantly. But why would you want to? It's nice inside the Clomper and there's tea.<br><br>How you organise the pipes and manage your steam is up to you. Balance steam output with heat build up. Too much heat and the boilers explode!<br><br>You repair the broken world by completing quests. Collect scrap to unlock new pipe shapes and grind it into resources you can spend on more pipes. Organise your pipe collection in your inventory book.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2349380/extras/a50afa82593e2447e0f62f430d9139b9.poster.avif?t=1759006490\" width=616 height=184 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2349380/extras/a50afa82593e2447e0f62f430d9139b9.webm?t=1759006490\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2349380/extras/a50afa82593e2447e0f62f430d9139b9.mp4?t=1759006490\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The world is procedurally generated, making the landscape surprising and fresh. Currently <i>very</i> simplistic pre-alpha developer graphics.<br><br>Take care when navigating the world, while the Clomper is strong the pipes and machines are not.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2349380/extras/c887acb6fa29f88efc750f3fd9f7cced.poster.avif?t=1759006490\" width=616 height=184 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2349380/extras/c887acb6fa29f88efc750f3fd9f7cced.webm?t=1759006490\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2349380/extras/c887acb6fa29f88efc750f3fd9f7cced.mp4?t=1759006490\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Clomper is a solo dev project by Rob Lang that has been built in the open in 5 years with over <strong>70 devlogs on YouTube! </strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Demo coming in 2025.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
